author: leosimons
msg: I have no idea where this bug was re-introduced (maybe it has to do with a different pmock or python version, I dunno), but the name verify() on the verifier object clashes with the verify() that pmock uses itself. This meant that I had to replace the mock_verifier that pmock supplied with a custom class that did the same thing. However, I managed to only half-remove the original pmock-based verify-the-verifier line and that resulted in a failing testcase.
